<F P=100> THE FORMER YUGOSLAV REPUBLIC OF MACEDONIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Greek Embargo Causes Standstill in Border Traffic </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2302090994 Skopje MIC in English 22 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2302090994 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje MIC </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Trucks Still Blocked"] </F>
  [Text] At the Greek border point Evzoni, on the 
Macedonian-Greek border, numerous trucks still remain blocked by 
the Greek authorities, due to the trade embargo. 
  For already the fifth day, cargo vehicles from Macedonia 
[The 
Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM], but also from a 
number of European Union member states, are waiting to exit 
Greece. The measure introduced by the Greek Government have 
grounded vehicles transporting a range of goods. 
  What will happen to them will be known after the European 
Union meeting, as there are no official explanations from the 
Greek side, which only adds to the indignation of the drivers. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

