<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Talks With Russians Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2202180494 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 1700 
GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2202180494 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Following a private meeting between the foreign 
ministers of Poland and Russia, Andrzej Olechowski and Andrey 
Kozyrev, talks between Foreign Ministry delegations began this 
afternoon at the provincial governor's office in Krakow. Taking 
part in the meeting are Ambassadors Stanislaw Ciosek and Yuriy 
Kashlev. According to earlier announcements, the plenary talks 
are devoted to seeking new forms of bilateral political and 
economic cooperation. Issues of European security, including 
the Partnership for Peace initiative, are also being discussed. 
  The Polish side is also expecting Minister Kozyrev to 
present 
a new concept of Russia's relations with the states of 
East-Central Europe. 
  The Russian foreign minister is on a two-day visit to 
Poland, 
which is taking place in Krakow. 

</TEXT>

