<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sejm Rejects Walesa's Constitutional Proposals </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1802195594 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 1800 
GMT 18 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1802195594 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] [Announcer] Today the Sejm rejected the presidential 
constitutional proposals. The president's press spokesman, 
Andrzej Drzycimski, acknowledged this to be a conflict between 
the party-dominated parliament and the president, who wanted to 
make it possible for all political forces and citizens to have a 
real role in the discussion on the Constitution. Sejm Speaker 
Jozef Oleksy addressed the statement by Andrzej Drzycimski 
during a news conference: 
  [Begin Oleksy recording] I do not think Poland needs any new 
conflict at the top, and Poles expect good cooperation from all 
of the highest bodies in authority in the state, a good mutual 
understanding of the matters that are most important for Poland, 
and not conflicts, collisions, rancor, and resentment. I wish 
to express a deep conviction that this sort of judgement 
expressed in the name of the president is an emotional judgement 
in association with the decision of parliament, and that it will 
not cast a shadow on the hitherto good cooperation between the 
president and the Sejm. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

