<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Oleksy: No Conflict Between Parliament, President </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1902202394 Warsaw TVP Television First Program Network in 
Polish 1830 GMT 19 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1902202394 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw TVP Television First Program Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Sejm Speaker Jozef Oleksy said in Czestochowa 
that Poland did not need a war at the top. This was his comment 
on the conflict between the president and parliament caused by 
the Sejm's rejection of Lech Walesa's proposal concerning the 
procedure of passing the Constitution. 
  [Begin Oleksy recording] I do not accept that a war at the 
top has started. I am opposed to this. I think that the 
president, whose spokesman's statement in a way sent a signal 
about such war, will think as I do and will make efforts to 
achieve harmonious cooperation between parliament and the 
president. Because, I stress, Poland does not need a war at the 
top. There have already been too many and they have spoiled too 
much. Poland needs reconciliation and common understanding in 
order to resolve problems of millions of people. [passage 
omitted] [end recording] 

</TEXT>

