<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Strak Says Draft Constitution `Badly' Prepared </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2002135794 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 0200 
GMT 20 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2002135794 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Michal Strak, the head of the Council of Ministers 
office, commenting on Lech Walesa's strong reaction to the 
Sejm's rejection of the presential draft laws regarding the 
so-called citizens' initiative on the Constitution, said that 
the president's officials had prepared this initiative badly and 
no one from the Belweder had discussed the draft with the Polish 
Peasant Party's parliamentary floor group. 
  Strak was speaking at a news conference in Gdansk. Earlier, 
Minister Strak held a meeting with students--members of the 
Political Ideas Club [Klub Mysli Politycznej]. During this 
meeting, he said, among other things, that his favorite hero was 
General Kutuzov, who, he said, slept during political and 
wartime debates but always woke up at the right moment. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

