<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Volunteers Defending Maglaj </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2302115994 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1100 GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2302115994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Hajrudin Sermic report from Maglaj] </F>
  [Text] Horrendous attacks of the chetnik-ustasha forces 
along the entire separating line on the Maglaj front are 
intensifying by the hour. The chetniks and ustashas are 
receiving reinforcements from Zepce, Doboj, Prnjavor, and Mt. 
Ozren. This are definitely the most powerful attacks so far 
with only one goal -- to conquer Maglaj. 
  The fighters of the 201st [Hill] Brigade have halted their 
further advances toward the town. An appeal by the Maglaj War 
Presidency and the Command of the 201st Hill Brigade of the 
Bosnia- Herzegovina Army to the residents that they immediately 
and urgently place themselves on the rim of the town and prevent 
the enemy from capturing Maglaj has borne fruit. Volunteers, 
representatives of the civilian authorities, more than 50 
mothers, and even wounded soldiers are reporting to participate 
in the crucial battle for Maglaj. They could not be prevented 
in this even by the hundreds of artillery shells fired at the 
town and several dozens of civilian casualties. The Maglaj is 
being defended heroically from the heart for who knows how long. 

</TEXT>

