<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serbs Reject Conditions for Opening Tuzla Airport </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2202191394 Belgrade TANJUG in English 1903 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2202191394 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Novi Sad, Feb 22 (TANJUG) -- Aleksa Buha, the 
foreign minister of the Bosnian Serb republic (RS), said on 
Tuesday that the talks on reopening the airport in the Moslem 
enclave of Tuzla should shortly begin and that this had already 
been discussed with Russian Deputy Foreign Minister Vitaliy 
Churkin in Sarajevo. 
  "However, the conditions for reopening the airport cannot be 
those proposed by French Foreign Minister Alain Juppe," because 
"his scenario for RS is unacceptable," Buha told Novi Sad radio. 
  Juppe has said that the west would even use force to reopen 
the Tuzla airport and threatened the Bosnian Serbs with NATO air 
strikes if they oppose this. 
  "Isn't the experience of the Sarajevo ultimatum sufficient 
warning to Mr. Juppe," Buha asked. 
  NATO threatened to launch air strikes against the warring 
sides in Sarajevo unless they withdraw their heavy artillery 
around Sarajevo to 20 km or place them under U.N. control but, 
in practice, these threats were directed against the local Serbs 
only. 
  However, the Bosnian Serbs started pulling out their heavy 
weaponry from around Sarajevo on Friday only at the initiative 
of Moscow and after it guaranteed to deploy its U.N. troops 
along the separation line with the Moslems. 
  The Bosnian Serb Republic agrees to reopen the Tuzla airport 
only if it receives guarantees that it will not be used to 
supply the Moslems with arms. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-31701 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu036_i_94008" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EEU-94-036 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  23 Feb 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ultimatum `Unacceptable' to Serbs </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2202162294 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1539 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2202162294 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Novi Sad, 22 Feb (TANJUG) -- Talks on opening Tuzla 
airport are expected to start soon and this was discussed in 
Sarajevo with Vitaliy Churkin, Russian deputy foreign minister, 
Aleksa Buha, the Serb Republic's (RS) foreign minister, told 
Novi Sad radio today. 
  "However, the opening of Tuzla airport will be permitted 
under the conditions somewhat different from those proposed by 
French Foreign Minister Alain Juppe, for his scenario is 
unacceptable for the RS. The French foreign minister has 
clearly indicated the West would like to apply the Sarajevo 
recipe, in the form of a NATO ultimatum, in the case of Tuzla 
airport. Was the experience of the Sarajevo ultimatum not 
sufficient for Mr Juppe?", Buha said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

