<H3> <TI>   Serbs Shell Tuzla Airport Area </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2202170194 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1600 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2202170194 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Salih Brkic report from Tuzla] </F>
  [Text] The chetnik shelling of the region around Tuzla is 
continuing. Last night and all today the Mt. Majevica chetniks 
have been pounding Vukovije and Dubrave with heavy artillery. 
They are firing the shells from the area of Poljanice on Mt. 
Majevica, and they have destroyed or badly damaged some dozen 
houses in Vukovije and Dubrave. It is obvious that the 
criminals from Mt. Majevica are showing that they are ready to 
fire at [Tuzla's] Dubrave Airport, which the world wants to open. 
  The general alarm has been sounded three times in Tuzla, and 
it is still in force. 
  Everything that has been happening around Tuzla these days 
shows that the decisions of the international community that 
Tuzla become a protected area are for the chetniks only a dead 
letter. 

</TEXT>

