<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   RSK Demands Equipment Withdrawal </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2202183094 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1748 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2202183094 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, 22 Feb (TANJUG) -- The government of the 
republic of Serb Krajina [RSK] today lodged a protest with the 
Zagreb-based UNPROFOR [UN Protection Forces] command because 
UNPROFOR lined up combat and technical equipment at its disposal 
along the Okucani-Sava bridge road near Stara Gradiska, whose 
barrels are directed toward the bridge, ISKRA [official Krajina 
news agency] reported this evening. 
  The Krajina Government demands that UNPROFOR withdraw all 
combat equipment within 24 hours, upon receipt of this demand, 
ISKRA reports. 
  To this effect, a meeting between representatives of the 
Krajina government and UNPROFOR should have been held today -- 
but UNPROFOR representatives informed through mediators that 
they would not be coming due to fears for their personal safety. 
  The RSK Government considers the failure of UNPROFOR 
representatives to show up as extremely frivolous, and the 
reasons stated as suspicious and provocative, the Krajina 
Government protest says, adding that the demonstration of force 
by UNPROFOR causes a feeling of fear among the Krajina 
population living on the territory of western Slavonia. The 
people of Krajina know well where the danger comes from and 
expect UNPROFOR to be deployed there, not on a bridge that 
connects the Serb people, the protest says in conclusion. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-31713 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu036_k_94004" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EEU-94-036 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  23 Feb 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Army Protests to UNPROFOR Over Serb Shelling </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2202182294 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1800 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2202182294 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The political department of the Croatian Army's 
operational zone of Split has reported that the Serbs repeatedly 
attacked Croatian Army's positions in the Zadar hinterland 
today. At around 1200, they fired several mortar shells on Kasic 
and Lakici. Between 1300 and 1420, they fired around 10 
artillery shells on the Maslenica area. At the same time they 
also fired on Novigrad. 
  The Croatian Army has protested to the UN Protection Force 
over these Serb attacks, the strongest in the last three months. 

