aggravating tensions in the region and presented a threat to the 
security of the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia. 
  The Albanian Government was demanded to re-examine its 
decision on the stationing of U.S. spy planes and placing its 
territory at NATO's disposal, in the interest of peace, 
stability, and the normalization of Yugoslav-Albanian ties. 

