<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Hungary </F>
<H3> <TI>   Liberal Parties Sign Election Agreement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2202181794 Budapest MTI in English 1648 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2202181794 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 22 February (MTI) -- Four parties -- the 
agrarian Federation, the Federation of Young Democrats (FIDESZ), 
the Liberal Civic Alliance (Entrepreneurs' Party), and the 
Alliance of Free Democrats (SZDSZ) -- signed an agreement on 
Tuesday [22 February] to set up a liberal election coalition, as 
preparation for the May elections. 
  The sides agreed that parties whose candidates cannot enter 
the second round because they received insufficient votes would 
support the candidate of the four parties to the agreement who 
won the most votes in the first round. 
  Inasmuch as candidates of several parties from those signing 
the agreement reach the second round, the number of votes cast 
for the candidates of the signatory parties will determine who 
will step down in favor of another candidate. 
  The parties will ensure that details of the agreement and 
the 
rules for stepping down be approved by their candidates. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

