<F P=100> ALBANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Berisha Offers To Help FYROM With Blockade </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1802172094 Tirana Radio Tirana Network in Albanian 1430 
GMT 18 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1802172094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana Radio Tirana Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Albanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The president's press and information office has 
just issued a report on President Berisha's meeting with the 
Macedonian foreign minister. 
  Albania is interested in stability in Macedonia [The Former 
Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM], President Berisha said 
at this meeting today. Albania is of the opinion that respect 
for all the rights of the Albanian population there is a 
condition for stability. Thus, the census and the opening of 
the Pedagogical School will be important steps in this 
direction. On the other hand, Berisha invites Albanian 
political forces to work for the stability of Macedonia, as this 
is in their interest, as well as that of the Albanian nation and 
the whole region. 
  President Berisha said that by exchanging greetings with 
President Gligorov, I want to assure you that Albania is ready 
to cooperate with you to increase the spirit of understanding 
and cooperation and establish them on sound bases. To overcome 
the blockade difficulties, Albania offers it all port and 
transport facilities and hopes that the conflicts between 
Macedonia and Greece can be overcome through dialogue. 
  Macedonian Foreign Minister Crvenkovski said that, by 
conveying President Gligorov's greetings to President Berisha, 
he would like to express the deep gratitude of our government 
for the support that Albania has given to Macedonia. We thank 
you for the facilities that you are creating for us at these 
difficult moments of the blockade. He again stressed his 
government's desire to strengthen cooperation with Albania. 
  Macedonian Foreign Minister Crvenkovski has ended his trip 
to 
our country. 

</TEXT>

