<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Swedish UNPROFOR Troops Near Tuzla Injured </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2202181094 Paris AFP in English 1757 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2202181094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Stockholm, Feb 22 (AFP) -- Five Swedish UN soldiers 
were injured Tuesday [22 February] when a grenade struck their 
tank north of Vares outside Tuzla, northeast Bosnia, the Swedish 
defence ministry said Tuesday. 
  Four of the the soldiers suffered shrapnel wounds, while one 
suffered eye injuries, Swedish defence ministry officials said. 
They were transported by helicopter to a Norwegian field 
hospital outside Tuzla. 
  It is not yet known who was responsible for the attack. Both 
Serbs and Moslems hold positions in the area. 
  It also uncertain whether the tank was targeted or hit by 
accident, Swedish defence ministry officials said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-31733 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu036_k_94001" </HT>


