<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Vacaroiu, Trade Unions Discuss Demands </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2402085794 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1800 GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2402085794 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Romanian Prime Minister Nicolae Vacaroiu met with 
representatives of the Cartel Alfa and the National Trade Union 
Bloc Confederations at Victoria Palace today. The meeting was 
attended by Mircea Dan Popescu, state minister and minister of 
labor and social protection; Emil Dima, president of the 
Administration Board of the State Property Fund; State Secretary 
Octavian Partenie, empowered by the government to handle 
relations with trade unions and employers; and states 
secretaries, directors, and experts from the Office for Liaison 
With Trade Unions and Employers and the Ministry of Labor and 
Social Protection. 
  The participants in the meeting discussed the conclusions 
drawn from negotiations on the points on the list of demands 
made by the two trade union confederations, especially the 
government's proposals to solve them. 
  Prime Minister Nicolae Vacaroiu presented the solutions 
proposed by the executive power to gradually solve the problems 
raised by the trade unions, which can be solved satisfactorily 
in the current economic situation. 
  The sides agreed on a greater involvement of trade unions in 
implementing the reform process, and especially in working out 
measures and solutions to alleviate social effects, a press 
release received from the Office for Liaison With Trade Unions 
and Employers attached to Romania's Government specifies. 

</TEXT>

