<H3> <TI>   SRI Director Replacing County Chiefs </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2402092294 Bucharest EVENIMENTUL ZILEI in Romanian 21 Feb 
94 p 4 </F>

<F P=103> AU2402092294 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest EVENIMENTUL ZILEI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Dan Andronic item: "Virgil Magureanu Replaces the SRI </F>
Heads in Valcea, Braila, and Galati"] 
  [Text] Virgil Magureanu, director of the Romanian 
Intelligence Service [SRI], visited the counties of Dolj and 
Gorj a few days ago to replace the chiefs of the SRI in those 
counties. The tour is continuing. 
  Virgil Magureanu yesterday replaced the SRI director in 
Valcea, the official reason being the inefficient use of state 
funds. Sources close to the SRI leadership have informed us that 
in the coming days Virgil Magureanu will visit the counties of 
Braila and Galati for the same purpose: to replace the chiefs 
of the SRI in these two counties. 
  It is worth mentioning that the five chiefs of SRI branches 
are joined by a further two such chiefs, who were replaced in 
the counties of Neamt and Vaslui a few weeks ago. 

</TEXT>

