<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Agreement Not Acceded to by Largest Trade Union </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2402092394 Bratislava HOSPODARSKE NOVINY in Slovak 22 Feb 
94 p 1 </F>

<F P=103> AU2402092394 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava HOSPODARSKE NOVINY </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by "sta": "KOVO Trade Union Did Not Accede"] </F>
  [Text] Bratislava -- The General Agreement between trade 
unions, employers, and the government for 1994 was signed 
without the KOVO [metal workers] trade union acceding to the 
document. V. Stevko, vice president of the Confederation of 
Trade Unions, said that the KOVO trade union does not feel bound 
by the agreement because its council placed it under a different 
obligation. "Unfortunately, at the time of negotiations, when 
the terms [of the agreement] had already been agreed upon, it is 
very difficult to speak about new talks," Stevko said, 
commenting on the decision of the KOVO Council. 

</TEXT>

