<H3> <TI>   Walesa Comments </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2302192594 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 1800 
GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2302192594 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Quotation marks denote recorded passages] </F>
  [Text] [Announcer] President Lech Walesa has said in Riga 
that he sees no point in future cooperation with the Sejm and is 
not going to talk with Sejm Speaker Jozef Oleksy about the 
conflict originating from the rejection of presidential 
constitutional proposals by the Sejm. Asked about his position 
on Aleksander Kwasniewski's statement that the president had no 
right to withdraw his representative from the Constitutional 
Commission, Lech Walesa said: 
  [Walesa] "If postcommunists and Kwasniewski were to have the 
real power, his idol Stalin would surely lock me up for that." 
  [Announcer] Lech Walesa said that he is ready to talk with 
the Sejm speaker about issues which have prospects for being 
resolved. 
  [Walesa] "The president has to talk and will talk with the 
speaker on issues which have prospects for being resolved. 
Nothing can be done on this issue of constitutional conflict, 
unless the speaker secures different voting." 
  [Announcer] President Walesa probably will not visit the 
Sejm 
building again. 
  [Walesa] "As I have noticed, there is no point, and I think 
that we are going to have ever fewer things in common." 

</TEXT>

