Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Foreign Ministry Demand"] </F>
  [Text] The Macedonian [The Former Yugoslav Republic of 
Macedonia -- FYROM] Foreign Ministry categorically refuted the 
France Press news on an alleged statement by Minister 
Crvenkovski during February 21 talks with the Netherlands 
counterpart Kooijmans, on Macedonia being ready to seek a 
compromise on the name issue, regardless of the latest trading 
embargo enforced by Athens. It is obvious that the word "not" 
is omitted after the word "Macedonia," without which the 
sentence makes no logical sense. Crvenkovski had explicitly 
stated in The Hague that Macedonia is ready to continue the 
negotiations with Greece, regardless of the Greek trading 
blockade imposed on Macedonia, the Foreign Ministry underlined. 

