<H3> <TI>   Denar Expected To Remain Stable </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2302183494 Skopje MILS-NEWS in English 23 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2302183494 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje MILS-NEWS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Denar Remains Stable"] </F>
  [Text] The 22 percent January inflation rate presents a 
deviation from the planned 8 percent one. The National Bank 
informs on a 1.5 percent January increase of the primary 
emission of cash, and predicts a possible 18 percent further 
increase in the first quarter of the year. The Bank will remain 
strictly on the planned projection, and this month's inflation 
rate is expected to be under the level planned with the 
stabilization program. 
  Owing to the restrictive policies and the increased supply 
of 
hard currency on the market, the denar can be expected to keep 
its stable course in reference to foreign currencies. 

</TEXT>

