<H3> <TI>   Plavsic Urges Serbs To Resist Tuzla Ultimatum </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2302180794 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1618 GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2302180794 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, 23 Feb (TANJUG) -- Srpska republic vice 
president Biljana Plavsic told SRNA [Bosnian Serb news agency] 
that if the Serbs succumbed to NATO's ultimatum-like demands for 
the opening of Tuzla airport, such pressure would turn into a 
common practice of snatching the remaining Serb territories in 
former Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
  According to her, the Serbs should condition the opening of 
Tuzla airport for humanitarian needs on the closure of land 
corridors bound for that town, which are now functioning 
perfectly well. 
  She added that the Serbs have aready paid a high price for 
conceding Sarajevo airport to the United Nations; this 
particularly refers to the transport of wounded Serbs, who now 
need three and a half hours to reach hospital instead of 30 
minutes as was the case before. 

</TEXT>

