<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by the Information Center of the 7th South </F>
Operations Group of the Bosnia-Herzegovina Army] 
  [Text] The enemy started tank-infantry attacks in the 
valleys of the rivers Bosna, Usora, and Spreca. Since this 
morning Maglaj and the surrounding area have been in the most 
serious situation. Namely, from several directions the aggressor 
has been using all available weapons in attacks on defense 
positions of the Maglaj defenders, the town center, and the 
surrounding area. This is actually the fiercest chetnik attack 
on the town since the beginning of the war. The enemy initiated 
these forceful attacks from Mt. Ozren, Brankovici, and Novi 
Seher. 
  The enemy has also been attacking free Doboj territories 
from 
several directions since this morning. From Mt. Ozren and all 
other strongholds the enemy has attempted a breakthrough at the 
river mouth [usce] near Doboj. The chetniks are also attacking 
free Tesanj territories, where the defense positions in [word 
indistinct] Kosa have been targeted from the direction of 
Vidkovac. 
  Members of the 110th Brigade of the Croatian Defense Council 
in Usora have also been defending their positions bravely this 
morning, as the chetniks have attempted breakthroughs in the 
region of Bandera. 
  There is no peace on free Teslic territories, where the 
defense positions of Teslic defenders and civilian settlements 
have been attacked. 

</TEXT>

