<H3> <TI>   Demirel Confirms Turkey Ready To Send Troops </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2302205594 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1800 GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2302205594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Here is a news item that has just arrived. 
President of the Bosnia-Herzegovina Presidency Alija 
Izetbegovic today held a telephone conversation with Turkish 
President Suleyman Demirel. The Turkish president conveyed to 
President Izetbegovic his country's readiness to send Turkish 
troops as a part of the UN Protection Forces [UNPROFOR] to help 
carry out the peace mission in Bosnia-Herzegovina. In reply to 
a question about the possible application of the Sarajevo model 
to other cities, Izetbegovic said that this model was acceptable 
with certain alterations which envisage the consistent 
implementation of Resolutions 824 and 836, which oblige the 
aggressor's side to place heavy weaponry under UNPROFOR control. 

</TEXT>

