<H3> <TI>   Inter-Muslim Clashes in Western Bosnia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2302160894 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1521 GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2302160894 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Petrovac, 23 Feb (TANJUG) -- According to the media 
in Velika Kladusa, members of the 5th Corps of the so-called 
Bosnia-Herzegovina army [loyal to Izetbegovic] have launched 
fierce attacks on positions held by the army of the autonomous 
province of Western Bosnia [loyal to Fikret Abdic] along the 
entire demarcation line. 
  According to both Velika Kladusa and Bihac, the fiercest 
clashes today took place in Trzacke Rastele and Pecigrad. 
Neither side has mentioned casualty tolls or changes in the 
frontlines. 
  Muslim radio in Bihac has appealed on several occasions 
today 
to supporters of Fikret Abdic to lay down their arms and place 
themselves at the disposal of the 5th Corps of Izetbegovic's 
army to defend the sovereignty and integrity of the Republic of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. 

</TEXT>

