<F P=100> YUGOSLAVIA </F>
<F P=101> Kosovo </F>
<H3> <TI>   Police Raid, Harass Ethnic Albanians </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2302205994 Tirana Radio Tirana Network in Albanian 1430 
GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2302205994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana Radio Tirana Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Albanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Albanian villages in Vushtrri commune have long 
been placed under strict police control. Reports confirm that 
the people in these villages live under conditions of complete 
siege, and that in every moment they are subject to checks and 
maltreatment by the Serbian police that this time do not 
hesitate to beat, raid, and arrest Albanians in the streets and 
everywhere they are. 
  Reports from Vushtrri inform that during the last two 
months, 
the Serbian police raided and harassed more than 60 Albanian 
families in Shtanoc in Poshtem village. Raids and massive 
harassments have been conducted in Zhilivol village. Last week, 
under the pretext of searching for arms, the Serbian police 
raided 13 families in Kacibek village in Podujeve. The police 
terror continues to escalate. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

