<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Croats, Muslims Agree to Cease-Fire </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2302190494 Zagreb HTV Television in Serbo-Croatian 1830 
GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2302190494 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb HTV Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Our colleague Zeljko Raic, who is covering the peace 
negotiations between General Ante Roso, commander of the 
Croatian Defense Council, and General Rasim Delic, commander of 
the Bosnia-Herzegovina Army, has just told us that a cease-fire 
agreement has been signed between the Croat and the Muslim sides 
in Bosnia-Herzegovina. The agreement takes effect on 25 
February. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

