<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Moravcik: Foreign Policy Not To Change </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2402143794 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1400 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2402143794 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1400 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] Jozef Moravcik granted an 
interview to TA SR. He noted that after the prime minister's 
proposal to dismiss him, presented to the president, and in view 
of the current political situation as well as the foreign 
political interests of the Slovak Republic, he considered it 
necessary to solve the personnel question of the minister of 
foreign affairs. At the same time, he did not assume that his 
departure would change Slovak foreign policy in principle 
because a change in political course would not be supported by 
parliament. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-31816 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu038_d_94003" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EEU-94-038 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  25 Feb 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Television Director Assumes Office </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2302163694 Bratislava NARODNA OBRODA in Slovak 22 Feb 94 p 
16 </F>

<F P=103> AU2302163694 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava NARODNA OBRODA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [TA SR report: "Ivan Stadtrucker in Office; New Slovak </F>
Television Director"] 
  [Text] Bratislava -- Ivan Gasparovic, chairman of the 
National Council of the Slovak Republic, introduced Ivan 
Stadtrucker into the office of central director of Slovak 
Television yesterday. He paid tribute to his practical and 
theoretical experience and expressed the wish that television 
should have mainly the viewer in mind and should not act as a 
political truncheon. Jozef Darmo, chairman of the Slovak 
Television Council, voiced his conviction that under the 
management of Ivan Stadtrucker, television broadcasts will meet 
the tasks arising from the law and will be constructive, 
politically tolerant, and of a high cultural standard. 

</TEXT>

