<H3> <TI>   Normalizing Relations With FRY Considered </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94P20404A Belgrade VECERNJE NOVOSTI in Serbo-Croatian 1 Feb 
94 p 5 </F>

<F P=103> 94P20404A </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade VECERNJE NOVOSTI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Offer to Belgrade?"] </F>
  [Text] Slovene Foreign Minister Lojze Peterle stated 
yesterday at a news conference that "Slovenia is considering 
normalizing relations with the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia 
[FRY]." According to Peterle, the Slovene Ministry of Foreign 
Affairs "is actively observing the state of everything that has 
recently changed in relations between Ljubljana and Belgrade." 
The diplomatic service in Slovenia is preparing information on 
what needs to be done to promote contacts between Ljubljana and 
Belgrade. Peterle pointed out that Slovenia's official position, 
favoring the normalizing of relations, is in Slovenia's 
interest, particularly because of the increasingly successful 
contacts between Zagreb and Belgrade. 

