Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Bosnia-Herzegovina Army 1st Corps report from Sarajevo] </F>
  [Text] The chetniks are continuing to violate the 
cease-fire flagrantly. They have again today provided enough 
evidence of the fact that they have not removed all the weaponry 
to the distance required. 
  This morning they fired with an antiaircraft machine gun 
from 
(Kromolje) at Brekin Potok, and small arms fire could be heard 
all day. This was particularly evident in Brijesce, Sokolje, 
Mijatovica Kosa, and Hotonj, while an antiaircraft gun from 
(Nadvozici) fired at (Visocje). 
  The Chetnik snipers have been active in various locations, 
where they have been seeking out victims using weapons with 
silencers. According to reports, there have been no casualties 
so far, but this behavior by the aggressor warrants extreme 
caution. 

