Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Mirza Sadikovic from Bihac] </F>
  [Text] On this the 19th day of the fiercest offensive on 
Bihac, the Serb aggressor continues his bestial orgy of 
destruction. The artillery and infantry, and tank and infantry 
attacks and attempts to break through on the Grmuski part of the 
front have continued today, as have attacks on (Hasino Brdo) and 
the Grmusko-Srbljanski Plateau, where the chetniks have again 
directed most of their forces. 
  They have been using a new method of shelling the town. 
Probably because of the increasingly frequent overflights of 
NATO aircraft, they have rescheduled their shelling of Cazin and 
Bihac with howitzers, tanks, and mortars from the hills 
surrounding Bihac to mornings and nights. 
  The defenders -- the heroes of the 5th Corps -- have been 
courageously resisting the attacks, defending with their bodies 
every inch of this blood-soaked land. Today they have repulsed 
several attempts at tank and infantry breakthroughs. 
  Today there have again been provocations along the 
demarcation lines with the remnants of the paramilitary of the 
so-called Kladusa autonomy, and the 5th Corps Command has lodged 
a strong protest with the UN Protection Forces [UNPROFOR], since 
the commander of the UN French Battalion promised to mediate and 
to take on responsibility for the observance of the latest 
cease-fire. 
  All in all, the [words indistinct] is continuing with a new 
uncertainty. 

</TEXT>

