<H3> <TI>   Vitez Suffers `Devastating' Artillery Attack </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2402190894 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1800 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2402190894 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ivica Saric reporting for Croatian Radio. Vitez is 
going through one of the most devastating Muslim artillery 
attacks since the aggression began on 15 April last year. The 
usual afternoon mortar provocations this evening turned into 
artillery barrage fire directed at the center of Vitez, the 
Croatian Defense Council's [HVO's] Vitez operational zone 
reports. 
  Tank-fired missiles and 122-mm howitzer shells are landing 
on 
residential areas and other civilian facilities. The attacks 
from the direction of Preocica and Poculica and other positions 
along the Zenica line have been coupled by 60-mm mortar shells 
from the direction of Mahala, the part of Stari Vitez under the 
control of the Muslim army. 
  The command of the Vitez operational zone reports that two 
children have already died in this infernal shelling. Nobody 
bothers to estimate the extent of the material damage any 
longer. The population has been warned by the local radio 
station and in other appropriate ways to descend into bomb 
shelters. The general alert sounded on 15 April last year is 
still in force. It is 1800 hours and the pounding goes on. HVO 
units are responding to the hostile fire with the means at their 
disposal, the Vitez operational zone command said. 

</TEXT>

