<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Muslims, Croats Agree To Exchange Prisoners </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2402215494 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
2100 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2402215494 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] An agreement on the exchange of prisoners has been 
reached at a meeting held in the HQ of UNPROFOR's [UN Protection 
Force] Spanish Battalion in Medjugorje between HVO [Croatian 
Defense Council] and Bosnia-Herzegovina army representatives. 
One thousand prisoners from Mostar, Jablanica, Prozor, Bogojno, 
Capljina and Stolac are to be exchanged. It was also agreed 
that the time and method for the exchange will be determined 
over the next few days in cooperation with the International Red 
Cross in Medjugorje. 

</TEXT>

