<F P=100> THE FORMER YUGOSLAV REPUBLIC OF MACEDONIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Greece's Reply Conveyed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2402173594 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1633 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2402173594 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Skopje, 24 Feb (TANJUG) -- Hans van den Broek, EU 
commissioner for foreign affairs, arrived in Skopje from Athens 
this afternoon to convey the Greek reply to a proposal that the 
Macedonian president sent to Greece yesterday on overcoming the 
dispute and the lifting of the Greek blockade. 
  Upon his arrival at Skopje's Petrovac airport, van den Broek 
stated that he was bringing some positive messages to Kiro 
Gligorov, president of Macedonia [The Former Yugoslav Republic 
of Macedonia -- FYROM], and the government. On the other hand, 
he added, much remained to be done, but in any case a dialogue 
must be restored in the forseeable future. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-31853 </DOCNO>
