<H3> <TI>   Minister Warns of Consequences of Blockade </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2402174894 Skopje MIC in English 24 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2402174894 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje MIC </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Grounded Goods -- Unforeseeable </F>
Consequences"] 
  [Text] Macedonia's [The Former Yugoslav Republic of 
Macedonia -- FYROM] Minister of Economy Petrus Stefanov informed 
the head of the CSCE monitoring mission in Macedonia, Norman 
Anderson, that vast quantities of goods of vital interest for 
the Macedonian economy were currently held at the Salonika port 
and other routes throughout Greece. 
  During their meeting they also discussed that large 
quantities of goods which are expected to arrive via Greece in 
the upcoming period, and concluded that if this situation 
continued, it would create unforeseeable consequences on the 
Macedonian economy. 

</TEXT>

