<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Discussions on Blockade </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2402162094 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1520 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2402162094 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, 24 Feb (TANJUG) -- Colonel Mark Wood, 
special envoy of the UN Protection Forces [UNPROFOR] commander 
for the former Yugoslavia, Jean Cot, today talked in Knin to 
representatives of the republic of Serb Krajina [RSK] about the 
problem of the Okucani bridge. 
  Citing unofficial sources, SRNA [news agancy] says that the 
bridge near Okucani linking RSK and the Srpska republic will be 
discussed tomorrow in Belgrade by Yasushi Akashi, special envoy 
of Butrus-Ghali, and RSK President Milan Martic. 
  This morning at about 0530 UNPROFOR units completely blocked 
all roads between western Slavonia and this bridge. The "blue 
helmets" denied access even to trucks carrying bread. 
  Several hundred citizens gathered at about 1100 near the 
bridge to protest against this blockade. 
  As we have unofficially learned in Knin, the members of the 
RSK ministry for internal affairs, who control the bridge, have 
no intention of abandoning it. At today's talks Colonel Wood 
received an offer whereby members of UNPROFOR may control the 
bridge along with Krajina's police, SRNA says. 

</TEXT>

