<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   HVO Attacks Convoy; UN Troops Return Fire </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2402154794 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1400 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2402154794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Colonel Bill Aikman, representative of the UN 
Protection Forces [UNPROFOR], stated today that the UN convoys 
had come under attack three times yesterday, once near Visoko 
and twice near Gornji Vakuf. He accused the HVO [Croatian 
Defense Council] of attacking convoys near Gornji Vakuf. On 
both occasions British troops escorting the convoys returned 
fire on the HVO positions, silencing the attackers. No 
casualties or serious damage was inflicted on the convoys. 
  The UN soldiers could not say with certainty who attacked 
the 
convoy on the Kiseljak-Visoko road, so they did not return fire, 
Colonel Aikman said. 

</TEXT>

