<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Karadzic, Abdic Sign Peace Agreement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2402204894 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1849 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2402204894 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, 24 Feb (TANJUG) -- Radovan Karadzic, 
president of the Srpska republic, and Fikret Abdic, the 
president of the autonomous province of western Bosnia, signed 
an agreement on guaranteeing peace along all borders and lines 
of separation. The agreement was signed in Belgrade today 
through the mediation of the President of Serbia Slobodan 
Milosevic. 
  The agreement was signed on the basis of a mutual commitment 
to restoring peace throughout the territory of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina as soon as possible, and in line with the 
Belgrade declaration of 22 October 1993, a statement says. 
  The text of the agreement is: 
  -- Peace is guaranteed along all borders of the autonomous 
province of Western Bosnia and the Srpska republic, along the 
entire line of separation between the forces of the autonomous 
province of Western Bosnia and the Srpska republic army, without 
exception. 
  When units of the national defense of the autonomous 
province 
of Western Bosnia are deployed on the section of the front from 
where the Fifth Corps of the Bosnia-Herzegovina army launches 
military actions against the Srpska republic army, permanent 
peace will immediately be established in this remaining sector 
of the front too. 
  -- Liaison officers, responsible for preventing incidents, 
have been appointed in all sectors on the line of separation 
between the forces of the autonomous province of Western Bosnia 
and the Srpska republic army. 
  -- The governments of the autonomous province of Western 
Bosnia and the Srpska republic will jointly provide conditions 
and undertake measures to enable communications links, traffic, 
and commerce between the autonomous province of Western Bosnia 
and the Srpska republic. 
  -- Borders between the autonomous province of Western Bosnia 
and the Srpska republic will be defined in line with the 
Belgrade declaration, and exclusively between the legal bodies 
of the autonomous province of Western Bosnia and the Srpska 
republic. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

