<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   UN's Akashi Meets With Martic, Milosevic </TI></H3>
<H4>   Serbs Agree To Withdraw From Bridge </H4>
<F P=102> LD2502172994 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1611 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2502172994 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, 25 February (TANJUG) -- The UN 
secretary-general's special envoy, Yasushi Akashi, and the 
president of the Republic of Serb Krajina, Milan Martic, reached 
an agreement in Belgrade today on the bridge between Gradiska 
and Stara Gradiska. They agreed that the situation on the 
bridge is to be restored to what it was on 18 February when the 
police of the Republic of Serb Krajina took control of the 
bridge from the UNPROFOR [UN Protection Forces]. 
  After one hour of talks, Akashi and Martic said that it was 
agreed that the UN peace forces are to withdraw armored 
personnel carriers deployed around the bridge over the past few 
days and that, at the same time, members of the ministry of 
internal affairs of the republic of Serb Krajina are to withdraw 
as well. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-31883 </DOCNO>
