<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Belgian Troops in Croatia Sent to Bosnia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2602192194 Brussels La Une Radio Network in French 1700 
GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2602192194 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels La Une Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] In Bosnia the cease-fire between Croats and 
Muslims has been respected on the whole, UN forces have said. 
[passage omitted] 
  Belgium will be sending UN soldiers. Soon 150 Belgian UN 
soldiers will leave Baranja, in eastern Croatia, for central 
Bosnia. A vanguard of a dozen Belgian soldiers has already 
left. The Belgian infantry is equipped with some 15 armored 
vehicles. The number of Belgian troops in Bosnia will thus 
total some 450 soldiers. 

</TEXT>

