<F P=100> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   NATO's Beard Finalizes Cooperation Program </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2502194094 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1700 
GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2502194094 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Bulgarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Robin Beard, NATO assistant secretary general for 
defense support, ended his two-day visit to Bulgaria today. 
Before leaving, he held a final meeting in Sofia with the 
President's Military Office, at which the participants exchanged 
information on the preparation of concrete programs for 
cooperation between Bulgaria and NATO under the Partnership for 
Peace initiative. 
  At a news briefing given at the Defense Ministry, Mr. Beard 
summed up the results of his visit, describing it as fruitful. 
During his visit, he said, he finalized a program for 
multilateral cooperation that will strengthen the links between 
Bulgaria and NATO. The program covers issues concerning the 
relations between civilian and military structures in the 
fulfillment of military programs and ways to implement state 
deliveries. It was agreed that three groups of NATO experts 
would visit Bulgaria with the task of providing assistance in 
information technology in connection with the administration of 
joint military programs. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

