<H3> <TI>   Goncz, Fur Comment on Army Preparedness </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2502173894 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
1500 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2502173894 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hungarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President Arpad Goncz, commander in chief of the 
armed forces, said that due to the southern Slav fighting, 
Hungarian soldiers must prepare themselves to defend peace. At 
a meeting with military leaders, Defense Minister Lajos Fur said 
that despite shrinking financial resources, the capability to 
mobilize and to react to unexpected challenges must be preserved. 
  In connection with the NATO Partnership for Peace, Fur 
stressed that it is in Hungary's basic interest to take 
advantage of this opportunity for cooperation since this will 
lead us to full membership. He said that it is necessary to 
prepare for joint training and joint military exercises, as well 
as Hungary's participation in peacekeeping. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

