<F P=100> HUNGARY </F>
<H3> <TI>   MDF To Follow Antall's Foreign Policies </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2502220594 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
1800 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2502220594 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hungarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The foreign affairs spokesman of the Hungarian 
Democratic Forum [MDF] has reaffirmed that the foreign policy 
that his party wishes to pursue is that hallmarked with the name 
of Jozsef Antall. The two main aims of this are European 
integration and the legal protection of Hungarians living beyond 
the borders. Gyorgy Csoti stressed that there is no better 
security guarantee than economic interconnections; for this 
reason the ruling party urges cooperation between the regions. 
In this endeavor, there is agreement between the parliamentary 
parties. The politician does not consider it likely that the 
Hungarian-Romanian and Hungarian-Slovak treaties will be signed 
in the near future because the two neighboring countries are not 
willing to accept minority protection guarantees. 

</TEXT>

