<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Condemns Hebron Shooting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2602164094 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1100 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2602164094 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] We will now present a statement by the Romanian 
Ministry of Foreign Affairs which states that it has learned 
about the abominable tragedy in the sacred establishment in 
Hebron in the West Bank, where scores of innocent people have 
become victims of insanity and intolerance, with profound 
concern. 
  The Ministry of Foreign Affairs most firmly condemns this 
criminal and irresponsible action just as it has condemned and 
continues to condemn any act of violence committed by the forces 
that oppose the easing of tensions in the Middle East. 
  The Ministry of Foreign Affairs expresses the hope that, 
despite this dramatic incident and other attempts to hamper the 
peace process, the desire by the sides to solve the conflict in 
this area by political means will continue with the same 
determination to capitalize on the favorable preconditions 
offered by the results of the bilateral Arab-Israeli 
negotiations in Washington, which have led to a mutual 
recognition between the PLO and Israel and to the signing of the 
principled declaration of 13 September 1993. 
  By virtue of its traditional relations in that area, Romania 
reiterates its readiness and interest in supporting the process 
of achieving peace, understanding, and economic cooperation in 
the Middle East, the statement by the Romanian Ministry of 
Foreign Affairs, which has been faxed to us, emphasizes in 
conclusion. 

</TEXT>

