<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mining Unions Announce Strike for 1 Mar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2602174094 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1100 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2602174094 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The National Federation of Mining Trade Unions of 
Romania affiliated to the Alfa Cartel has faxed us a communique 
in which it announces that the trade union leaders from all 
mining basins, except for the Jiu Valley, who held a meeting in 
Caciulata from 24-25 February, decided to organize a one-day 
general strike on 1 March, starting right at the beginning of 
the first shift. 
  In this way, the trade unions in the mining and geological 
industry support the demands made by the Mining Trade Union 
Federation and the Alfa Cartel, the communique signed by the 
president of the federation specifies. 
  The Autonomous Civil and Municipal Construction Trade Union 
Federation has also informed us in a communique that it will 
participate in the one-day strike on 28 February, together with 
the CNSLR [National Confederation of Romania's Free Trade 
Unions] Fratia Confederation, of which it is a member. 

</TEXT>

