<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   PNTCD Chairman on Coalition Possibilities </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2502160494 Bucharest TINERETUL LIBER in Romanian 23 Feb 94 
p 3 </F>

<F P=103> AU2502160494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest TINERETUL LIBER </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Bogdan Tiberiu Iacob: "Despite the Rumors That </F>
Are Being Circulated, Mr. Coposu Remains Firm: `PNTCD Will Not 
Join the Government Without CDR'"] 
  [Text] In a dialogue with our correspondents yesterday, 
Corneliu Coposu, PNTCD [National Peasant Christian-Democratic 
Party] chairman, categorically refuted the rumors that are being 
circulated alleging that certain so-called changes occurred in 
his political-strategic position. "As far as we are concerned, 
no changes have occurred," the PNTCD leader said. "We decided 
to answer favorably to the invitation addressed to us by Oliviu 
Gherman [chairman of the Social Democracy Party of Romania -- 
PDSR] to engage in a dialogue with the PDSR separately from the 
rest of the CDR [Democratic Convention of Romania], but we will 
not join the government without our allies within the CDR, and 
that could also happen only if Ion Iliescu renounces his 
monopoly over the country's authorities. We refuse the idea of 
setting up a national unity government and we will not cooperate 
with the extremist parties -- the PRM [Greater Romania Party], 
the PSM [Socialist Party of Labor], and the PUNR [National 
Romanian Unity Party]. As far as the UDMR [Democratic Union of 
Hungarians in Romania] is concerned, our relations with them 
have not cooled down at all; they are the same as before. The 
UDMR remains our ally, despite our reserve regarding their 
program and the draft they elaborated for the ethnic minority 
bill." 

</TEXT>

