<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cardoso Not To Resign </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2901003294 Brasilia Voz do Brasil Network in Portuguese 
2100 GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2901003294 </F>
<F P=104>  Brasilia Voz do Brasil Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Finance Minister Fernando Henrique Cardoso said 
today that he will not leave his post following the government 
defeat in Congress. He added the government will maintain all 
the agreements signed for the approval of the economic plan. 
  Minister Cardoso said that the commitment the government 
needs from Congress is a zero deficit this year. He explained 
that there are conditions to compensate, via other measures, for 
the resources that would have been collected with the income tax 
increase on large companies and the financial operations tax 
which were not approved by Congress. 
  [Begin Cardoso recording] From the point of view of numbers, 
there is no problem in replacing what was denied, but this 
something else cannot come from the workers or from the middle 
class; it must come from companies because they benefited from 
the decision of the minority in the Chamber of Deputies 
yesterday which opposed the approval of the tax rate increase on 
companies, which was a small rate. I reaffirm that the struggle 
against inflation is everyone's struggle for the benefit of the 
Brazilian people because there are favorable conditions for 
investment in Brazil -- the time is right. But this is 
everyone's struggle, otherwise inflation will not be defeated. 
[end recording] 
  Cardoso also said that the government will continue to 
fulfill the agreements reached during the negotiations for the 
approval of the economic plan. He added that in the amendment 
for the creation of the social emergency fund, the states will 
also be excluded, like what happened to the municipalities 
following the retention of the participation fund. Cardoso 
explained that in exchange for the retention the states accepted 
a cut in the budget program equivalent to $200 million. The 
fund will also receive the PIS [Social Integration Program] 
revenue from the banks. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

