Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Strong security measures have been taken around the 
National Palace to prevent any confrontation with the peasants 
who are marching to the central plaza. Approximately 200 
policemen have been deployed in the capital's downtown area to 
prevent violence by demonstrators and infiltrators. The 
decorative streetlights outside the National Palace have been 
removed to keep them from being damaged if disturbances break 
out. 
  Here is a report by Ana Julieta Cardenas. 
  [Begin recording] [Cardenas] It was reported from the 
National Palace that there is normal activity around the area 
despite increased security by National Police personnel and 
soldiers who regularly guard the building. People are entering 
and leaving the building without any problem. The government 
minister has said that the security troops are on alert to 
forestall any possible disturbances. He is going to report on 
the reaction by government offices to the strike announced by 
the workers. 
  [Government Minister Arnoldo Ortiz] [Words indistinct] on 
the 
strike that was announced [words indistinct] study on economy 
reveals it is totally normal. Communications are totally normal. 
Postal service is completely normal. Everything appears normal 
in the capital. [Words indistinct] everything is reported to be 
normal. [Words indistinct] first appearance was that there was 
strike announced. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

