<F P=100> Guatemala </F>
<H3> <TI>   De Leon on Talks With New Honduran President </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2901030794 Guatemala City Cadena de Emisoras Unidas in 
Spanish 0015 GMT 29 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2901030794 </F>
<F P=104>  Guatemala City Cadena de Emisoras Unidas </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement by Guatemalan President Ramiro de Leon Carpio </F>
during a news conference upon his return from Honduras; at the 
Guatemalan Air Force Base's Protocol Room in Guatemala City on 
28 January -- recorded] 
  [Text] Honduras and Guatemala have to fight poverty and 
corruption as one of the most serious problems faced by our 
nations. We have to show honesty and political determination, 
which, as I said before, will lead to closer relations between 
both countries. President Reina and I held a brief working 
meeting at the airport. I also held working meetings with the 
president and the rest of the Central American presidents. 
There is complete agreement on the principles of austerity, 
honesty, and the fight against corruption. We need to give a 
human and social image to our economic growth, which should have 
a distribution with social equality. I believe there is a 
complete identification with the new Honduran president. 

</TEXT>

