  The president-elect stated that there has been no pressure 
whatsoever behind these appointments. 
  [Begin Frei recording] I would like to say once again that I 
have not been pressured to make any of these appointments. 
Undoubtedly, the various political parties have conveyed their 
suggestions and I have talked to the ministers, but everybody 
left me free to make the appointments. As I have explained, the 
delay -- which I believe to be perfectly normal given the fact 
that I was operated on just a week ago -- in making these 
appointments gave me the chance to talk to all of them and make 
sure that they will do their jobs independently. [end recording] 

